============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is a programming language?
A1: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q2: What is metabolism?
A2: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q3: What is osmosis?
A3: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q4: What is evolution?
A4: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q5: What is machine learning?
A5: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

