  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Confucius
Lived:         551 - -479
Nationality:   Chinese
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Confucianism
Contribution:  Ren, li, filial piety; still shapes East Asian society 2,500 years later
Quote:         "It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop."

Name:          Charles Darwin
Lived:         1809 - 1882
Nationality:   English
Field:         Biology
Known For:     Evolution by Natural Selection
Contribution:  On the Origin of Species; explained diversity of life on Earth
Quote:         "It is not the strongest that survives, but the most adaptable."

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

